WEBVTT

00:01.835 --> 00:03.904
Previously on This Is Us...

00:03.937 --> 00:06.640
I don't see her making it
through the night.

00:06.674 --> 00:08.176
RANDALL:
We're good now.

00:08.209 --> 00:10.711
You made us good.

00:10.744 --> 00:13.013
You tell him hey.

00:16.350 --> 00:17.551
Hey.

00:18.586 --> 00:19.653
Hey.

00:19.687 --> 00:21.589
I'm pregnant.

00:21.622 --> 00:23.257
You're gonna be a grandfather.

00:23.291 --> 00:26.760
I'm not worried about
forgetting about the big stuff.

00:26.794 --> 00:29.263
It's the regular...

00:29.297 --> 00:31.399
Saturday
when the kids were little,

00:31.432 --> 00:34.001
a day when nothing big
really happened.

00:34.034 --> 00:35.736
We were just laughing

00:35.769 --> 00:38.038
and playing
pin the tail on the donkey.

00:38.072 --> 00:40.641
That's the stuff
I'm not ready to let go of yet.

00:41.809 --> 00:44.145
(birds chirping)

00:57.458 --> 01:00.328
-Mm. Hey.
-Hey.

01:01.629 --> 01:03.063
Mm.

01:04.165 --> 01:06.167
(takes deep breath)

01:07.635 --> 01:11.439
Did you know you have
a tiny little scar

01:11.472 --> 01:14.007
-underneath your eyebrow?
-Mm-hmm. Yeah.

01:15.008 --> 01:16.977
Yeah.

01:17.010 --> 01:19.947
I never noticed it before.

01:19.980 --> 01:21.782
Yeah. (inhales deeply)

01:21.815 --> 01:25.052
It comes out
when I'm in the sun,

01:25.085 --> 01:27.121
and I got a little sun
the other day.

01:27.155 --> 01:30.591
I can't believe
I never noticed it.

01:32.993 --> 01:35.629
(clears throat) So...

01:35.663 --> 01:37.631
-when I was a little girl...
-Mm-hmm.

01:37.665 --> 01:39.633
...there was this little
playground right by my house

01:39.667 --> 01:42.303
that my dad would take me to
sometimes,

01:42.336 --> 01:46.140
and it had one of
those really lame slides

01:46.174 --> 01:48.942
-that would give you burn marks
on your butt. Mm-hmm.
-Oh, yeah. Yeah.

01:48.976 --> 01:50.944
And, um, you know,

01:50.978 --> 01:53.113
one of those weird
old rocking horse things

01:53.147 --> 01:54.615
that only had one eye.

01:54.648 --> 01:56.517
The springy ones.

01:56.550 --> 01:58.486
-Yeah, yeah.
-Totally creeped me out.

01:58.519 --> 02:03.291
But then
there was this one swing.

02:03.324 --> 02:05.159
God, I loved that swing.

02:06.860 --> 02:09.663
And he would push me on it.

02:09.697 --> 02:13.100
And one time,
I remember I turned around

02:13.133 --> 02:16.204
on the way back down, and
my dad wasn't paying attention,

02:16.237 --> 02:19.973
and his watch clocked me
right above the eye.

02:20.007 --> 02:21.475
Hmm.

02:21.509 --> 02:23.611
He felt so bad,

02:23.644 --> 02:27.181
but I didn't care because
him pushing me in that swing

02:27.215 --> 02:28.716
was just my favorite thing

02:28.749 --> 02:30.050
in the entire world, you know?

02:30.083 --> 02:33.287
DAVE:
And we swing.

02:33.321 --> 02:37.157
It was such a treat for me,
going there with him.

02:38.859 --> 02:40.494
But I would just-- I'd spend

02:40.528 --> 02:44.565
the entire time
worrying about when...

02:46.367 --> 02:49.637
...he would stop pushing me,

02:49.670 --> 02:52.273
when he'd say
that it was time to go home.

02:56.009 --> 02:58.812
Really wish that I had spent
more time appreciating it

02:58.846 --> 03:01.482
when it was all happening,

03:01.515 --> 03:04.585
instead of just...

03:04.618 --> 03:07.321
worrying about
when it would end.

03:07.355 --> 03:09.323
Hmm.

03:09.357 --> 03:11.892
At least I still have the scar.

03:14.462 --> 03:16.930
(sighs) Oh.

03:16.964 --> 03:18.732
-Hmm.
-Um...

03:18.766 --> 03:20.167
Randall's math thing
got canceled today,

03:20.200 --> 03:23.537
so we have a completely free
Saturday with no plans.

03:24.572 --> 03:27.107
No football games,
no playdates.

03:27.140 --> 03:29.042
What should we do?

03:30.143 --> 03:31.445
Nothing.

03:31.479 --> 03:32.946
-Nothing.
-Mm-hmm.

03:32.980 --> 03:37.084
Oh, nothing sounds so nice.

03:37.117 --> 03:38.786
-Yeah.
-Yeah.

03:41.154 --> 03:43.824
And swing, Rebecca.

03:46.594 --> 03:49.463
And we swing.

03:49.497 --> 03:52.433
-Ready, Randall? (whoops)
-Kate, touch the sky.

03:52.466 --> 03:54.067
-And we swing!
-Touch the sky with your feet.

03:54.101 --> 03:55.102
There you go.

03:55.135 --> 03:57.471
*

03:58.306 --> 04:01.642
-And we swing!
-(chuckles)

04:01.675 --> 04:03.877
-Higher!
-And we swing!

04:03.911 --> 04:04.878
(Beth whoops)

04:04.912 --> 04:06.614
(Kevin laughs)

04:06.647 --> 04:08.882
Swing. Throw your arms up.
(whooshes)

04:08.916 --> 04:11.652
*

04:13.654 --> 04:15.323
-Whee!
-(Toby speaks indistinctly)

04:15.356 --> 04:17.891
-(Kate laughs)
-(gasps)

04:17.925 --> 04:18.959
All right, Hope. Ready?

04:18.992 --> 04:20.394
BOTH:
Back and forth,

04:20.428 --> 04:23.230
and we swing!

04:23.263 --> 04:25.733
-And swing!
-Swing. (chuckles)

04:25.766 --> 04:27.801
*

04:37.678 --> 04:39.480
(birds chirping)

04:43.651 --> 04:45.519
(clicks tongue)

04:45.553 --> 04:47.187
(sighs)

04:49.823 --> 04:51.859
*

05:01.802 --> 05:03.837
*

05:14.815 --> 05:16.484
(sighs)

05:29.930 --> 05:31.599
(chuckles softly)

05:43.777 --> 05:45.846
*

05:52.219 --> 05:53.186
JACK:
Hey, guys!

05:53.220 --> 05:54.455
Breakfast!

05:58.792 --> 06:00.861
-(lively chatter)
-Attention. Hello.

06:00.894 --> 06:02.095
-JACK: Mmm. Okay, Mom's up.
-So...

06:02.129 --> 06:04.264
since Randall's math contest
got canceled...

06:04.297 --> 06:06.366
-Mathletes.
-What?

06:06.400 --> 06:09.102
It's Mathletes,
and it's not a contest.

06:09.136 --> 06:10.438
It's a group of math enthusiasts

06:10.471 --> 06:12.973
who perform and compete
at a, um...

06:14.975 --> 06:16.410
Forget it.
I'll talk about it later.

06:16.444 --> 06:18.746
-Go ahead.
-It just means we have

06:18.779 --> 06:20.247
a completely free Saturday.

06:20.280 --> 06:21.449
Just us.

06:21.482 --> 06:22.950
(groans)

06:22.983 --> 06:24.785
JACK: Oh, what? Come on.
Is it really that hard

06:24.818 --> 06:27.187
-to be all together for a day?
-RANDALL AND KATE: Mm-hmm.

06:27.220 --> 06:29.356
-Yes.
-(Kate snickers)

06:29.389 --> 06:32.460
REBECCA: Okay, well,
what do you guys want to do?

06:32.493 --> 06:35.362
-Whatever.
-KEVIN: Don't care.
-(scoffs) O-Okay.

06:35.395 --> 06:37.130
Katie girl, what do you got?

06:37.164 --> 06:38.732
Anything we want?

06:38.766 --> 06:40.100
-Mm-hmm.
-All day?

06:40.133 --> 06:42.603
Anything you want. All day.

06:42.636 --> 06:43.837
What do you got, Katie girl?

06:45.138 --> 06:46.440
-Several ideas.
-REBECCA: Oh, well, there we go.

06:46.474 --> 06:47.775
Several ideas.

06:47.808 --> 06:49.309
-Okay. I like that.
-JACK: She's got ideas.

06:49.342 --> 06:51.311
I like, I like people
with several ideas.

06:51.344 --> 06:53.614
(overlapping chatter)

06:53.647 --> 06:55.516
(Randall sighs)

06:56.817 --> 06:59.119
How's the writing coming?

06:59.152 --> 07:00.320
Slowly.

07:02.956 --> 07:06.660
-Thanks.
-Service is in, uh,
less than two hours.

07:07.795 --> 07:09.162
I'm aware.

07:13.467 --> 07:15.435
(sighs heavily)

07:20.273 --> 07:21.241
What?

07:21.274 --> 07:23.010
Nothing.

07:23.043 --> 07:24.845
I'm just checking on you.

07:24.878 --> 07:26.547
I'm good.

07:27.615 --> 07:29.650
(scribbling on paper)

07:31.852 --> 07:33.320
(pen clatters)

07:33.353 --> 07:34.555
What, woman?

07:35.556 --> 07:38.358
I think we need to bang out
a worst-case scenario.

07:38.391 --> 07:40.494
-About what?
-You.

07:42.195 --> 07:43.864
You go first.

07:43.897 --> 07:46.299
I don't even know what
we're worst-case scenario-ing.

07:46.333 --> 07:49.637
After burying your fourth
and final parent, you lose it.

07:49.670 --> 07:52.472
No parents left to bury,
you spend the rest of your days

07:52.506 --> 07:54.107
going to other people's
parents' funerals.

07:54.141 --> 07:56.176
Just crying single tears

07:56.209 --> 07:58.646
at funerals of parents
you don't even know.

07:58.679 --> 07:59.847
Go.

08:01.014 --> 08:02.315
I really don't think
I'm gonna be going to...

08:02.349 --> 08:04.785
You buy an RV. (clicks tongue)

08:04.818 --> 08:06.720
Wake up one morning and say,
"Beth, we need an RV."

08:06.754 --> 08:08.956
I say, "Sure, I can get down
with an RV."

08:08.989 --> 08:11.358
You spend the rest of your days
traveling back and forth

08:11.391 --> 08:13.193
between your parents'
various resting places,

08:13.226 --> 08:15.596
just driving from tree to tree.

08:16.564 --> 08:18.632
-Baby, I'm...
-Mind you,

08:18.666 --> 08:20.400
I didn't even mention Miguel.

08:20.433 --> 08:23.036
I just realized that.
Maybe you realize it, too.

08:23.070 --> 08:25.739
-You decide you need
to go to Puerto Rico.
-(scoffs)

08:25.773 --> 08:28.709
Try and learn about his deceased
great-grandmother's story,

08:28.742 --> 08:29.910
come back talking about
swimming in the Atlantic Ocean

08:29.943 --> 08:31.311
with Miguel's
great-grandmama's ghost.

08:31.344 --> 08:32.680
-And I'm thinking to myself...
-Uh, Beth. I'm okay.

08:34.281 --> 08:36.483
I am appropriately sad,

08:36.516 --> 08:40.187
and I am appropriately anxious
about this eulogy.

08:40.220 --> 08:42.189
All right?

08:42.222 --> 08:43.991
I'm centered,

08:44.024 --> 08:47.394
and I'm looking forward
to this quiet next chapter

08:47.427 --> 08:51.098
with my wife and our lives,

08:51.131 --> 08:53.634
and our eventual grandchildren.

08:55.135 --> 08:57.971
Have you made a decision
about deep-fried Oreos?

08:58.939 --> 09:01.609
(takes deep breath)

09:01.642 --> 09:03.944
Musing.

09:03.977 --> 09:05.212
You?

09:06.213 --> 09:07.815
Same.

09:08.816 --> 09:11.284
REBECCA:
Hey, Bug, these lines looking
straight enough to you?

09:11.318 --> 09:14.287
-Yep. Perfect.
-Great.

09:14.321 --> 09:18.191
I don't want to play four square
with my parents. It's lame.

09:18.225 --> 09:20.060
Yeah, well,
you should have contributed

09:20.093 --> 09:21.394
to the suggestions, then, Kev.

09:21.428 --> 09:23.430
Kevin's right, this is stupid.

09:25.165 --> 09:26.266
What is it with you two today?

09:27.167 --> 09:28.869
Hey, ladies.

09:28.902 --> 09:31.138
Coming to check
on your chalk work.

09:31.171 --> 09:33.841
*

09:45.185 --> 09:46.820
REBECCA:
Whoa. Oh. Right?

09:46.854 --> 09:48.922
That was an assist.
That was an assist.

09:48.956 --> 09:50.123
-(Rebecca whoops)
-(Jack laughs)

09:50.157 --> 09:52.225
-(Rebecca chuckles)
-Four big ones.

09:52.259 --> 09:54.461
*

09:54.494 --> 09:56.463
(footsteps approaching)

09:56.496 --> 09:58.298
(chuckles softly)

10:05.505 --> 10:08.308
If it's okay with you,
I would like to say three things

10:08.341 --> 10:11.344
that will surely cross
multiple ex-husband lines

10:11.378 --> 10:13.046
and protocols.

10:14.848 --> 10:16.950
-Proceed.
-Okay.

10:16.984 --> 10:18.218
Number one.

10:20.320 --> 10:23.691
She was extraordinarily
proud of you.

10:25.893 --> 10:28.796
I am extraordinarily
proud of you.

10:28.829 --> 10:30.030
That was number two.

10:30.063 --> 10:32.165
They get progressively
more and more intense

10:32.199 --> 10:34.034
-as we go.
-Gotcha.

10:34.067 --> 10:36.136
And the third one is
a real doozy.

10:37.537 --> 10:38.872
Today is a doozy.

10:38.906 --> 10:41.441
So...

10:41.474 --> 10:44.011
I love you, kid.

10:46.479 --> 10:48.816
I love you.

10:49.817 --> 10:51.518
And even though our marriage
didn't go the distance,

10:51.551 --> 10:53.687
if Doc Brown showed up right now

10:53.721 --> 10:55.522
and offered me a ride
in the DeLorean,

10:55.555 --> 10:57.891
I would go right back to
that weight loss support group

10:57.925 --> 11:00.193
and make stupid faces at you.

11:00.227 --> 11:02.029
(chuckles)

11:02.062 --> 11:03.463
(distant chatter and laughter)

11:03.496 --> 11:04.965
That's
a Back to the Future reference.

11:04.998 --> 11:06.767
I know, I was married to you.

11:08.168 --> 11:09.269
Yes, you were.

11:13.006 --> 11:15.175
Yes, I was.

11:29.122 --> 11:30.690
(door opens)

11:32.092 --> 11:35.095
Kate? Kate.

11:35.128 --> 11:38.799
Thought you wanted to watch
the home movies next, right?

11:43.804 --> 11:45.605
It's raining pretty hard, huh?

11:49.977 --> 11:52.479
Hey, how about we play a game
next weekend?

11:54.447 --> 11:57.250
Better yet, how about you play
and I'll watch?

11:57.284 --> 11:59.787
I really just like
being together.

11:59.820 --> 12:03.456
Plus, only four people can play,

12:03.490 --> 12:05.793
and I just slow the game down.

12:05.826 --> 12:08.461
That's okay.

12:08.495 --> 12:13.333
I mean, all I want nowadays is
to slow things down anyway.

12:14.334 --> 12:15.936
Me, too.

12:18.438 --> 12:20.140
Home movies?

12:20.173 --> 12:22.309
-Home movies.
-Okay.

12:27.480 --> 12:28.648
(sighs)

12:31.318 --> 12:34.454
-KIDS: We love cake!
-REBECCA: One, two, three.

12:34.487 --> 12:35.923
Oh, wait. Wait, wait,
wait, wait.

12:35.956 --> 12:38.792
This-this is it.
This. Is. The. One.

12:38.826 --> 12:40.627
(VCR whirs)

12:42.762 --> 12:44.497
(Rebecca gasps)

12:44.531 --> 12:46.299
(chuckles)

12:46.333 --> 12:47.901
-REBECCA: No way.
-JACK: Uh-huh.

12:47.935 --> 12:49.169
(dishes clatter on video)

12:49.202 --> 12:50.503
Come on, not on camera, please.

12:50.537 --> 12:52.639
I'm a mess.
I'm covered in sauce.

12:52.672 --> 12:54.641
-Yeah. Oh, yeah. You know what?
You're revolting, okay?
-(chuckles)

12:54.674 --> 12:55.843
I... I want to show you
something

12:55.876 --> 12:57.110
that I've been working on.

12:57.144 --> 12:58.611
Can I just finish the dishes
first, please?

12:58.645 --> 13:00.080
Nope. Get ready.

13:00.113 --> 13:01.681
-Hey, Big Three.
-(Rebecca chuckles)

13:01.714 --> 13:03.316
Enter.

13:03.350 --> 13:04.784
Come on, come on. Come on in,
come on in.

13:04.818 --> 13:06.119
Come on in. Come on in.

13:06.153 --> 13:07.287
(Jack laughs)

13:07.320 --> 13:08.788
Come on in. Come on in, Kev.

13:08.822 --> 13:11.291
-Ready?
-BIG THREE: Ready!

13:11.324 --> 13:12.292
REBECCA:
Look at you guys.

13:12.325 --> 13:14.294
How are you that little?

13:14.327 --> 13:15.863
-JACK: So tiny.
-Look how cute you were, Kev.

13:15.896 --> 13:17.865
JACK (on video):
Ready. First came...

13:17.898 --> 13:19.366
Me.

13:19.399 --> 13:21.468
-JACK: And Dad said...
-"Gee."

13:21.501 --> 13:22.936
-JACK: And then came...
-Me.

13:22.970 --> 13:24.537
-JACK: And Mom said...
-"We."

13:24.571 --> 13:26.106
-JACK: And then came...
-Me.

13:26.139 --> 13:28.141
-JACK: And we said...
-"That's three."

13:28.175 --> 13:29.376
JACK:
Big Three.

13:29.409 --> 13:31.478
ALL:
Big Three!

13:31.511 --> 13:32.980
Ah!

13:33.013 --> 13:34.614
Jack, are you kidding me?

13:34.647 --> 13:36.349
How long did that take?

13:36.383 --> 13:37.617
JACK:
Oh, that was, uh...

13:37.650 --> 13:40.053
that was l-less than
potty training

13:40.087 --> 13:41.621
-but longer than the ABCs.
-(gasps)

13:41.654 --> 13:43.823
You guys are so good!

13:43.857 --> 13:45.125
-Come give me hugs.
-REBECCA: Little Kev.
-JACK: Yeah.

13:45.158 --> 13:47.294
-REBECCA: Kev, look.
-Kevin, look.

13:47.327 --> 13:49.129
REBECCA (on video):
Oh, my goodness.
You're so smart.

13:49.162 --> 13:50.530
I've seen this
like a million times.

13:50.563 --> 13:52.465
-Yeah.
-(Rebecca scoffs)

13:52.499 --> 13:53.833
I'm gonna go upstairs.

13:55.202 --> 13:56.736
Today sucks.

13:57.770 --> 14:00.140
(chatter on video continues)

14:00.173 --> 14:02.509
Two rays of sunshine.

14:03.510 --> 14:05.512
Knock, knock.

14:06.679 --> 14:08.748
-KEVIN: Go away.
-(scoffs)

14:09.849 --> 14:12.552
Uh-uh. Enough, Kev. Okay?

14:13.853 --> 14:16.523
Hey. What's going on, bud?

14:22.795 --> 14:25.565
Yesterday we did
the President Fitness thing.

14:25.598 --> 14:27.767
Uh-huh.

14:27.800 --> 14:30.870
I got the best time in the mile,
and I did the most sit-ups.

14:30.904 --> 14:33.540
I did just whatever
on the sit and reach, but...

14:33.573 --> 14:35.608
that's for girls anyway,
so who cares.

14:36.743 --> 14:38.912
So, what's the problem?

14:38.946 --> 14:41.614
I couldn't do any pull-ups.

14:41.648 --> 14:44.317
I've just never been
able to do them.

14:46.319 --> 14:50.190
So you can't do a pull-up.
What's the big deal?

14:50.223 --> 14:53.961
I was just hanging there
for, like, two minutes,

14:53.994 --> 14:56.029
and everyone was laughing.

14:56.063 --> 14:58.531
At me. They were laughing at me,
Mom.

14:58.565 --> 15:00.467
Okay. (clears throat)

15:00.500 --> 15:02.302
First of all,

15:02.335 --> 15:05.072
I'm sure no one was
laughing at you.

15:06.306 --> 15:09.576
Yeah. Maybe not.

15:09.609 --> 15:11.911
Plus, I had Sophie tell
a bunch of the girls

15:11.945 --> 15:14.948
that I was faking it,
so all the unathletic kids

15:14.982 --> 15:16.783
didn't feel bad
when they couldn't do one.

15:17.985 --> 15:20.120
It played.

15:20.153 --> 15:22.755
Ugh. Kevin.

15:23.756 --> 15:26.193
I really just couldn't do one,
Mom.

15:27.194 --> 15:29.729
Yeah.

15:29.762 --> 15:32.465
But that's okay.

15:32.499 --> 15:35.768
You know, not everything is
gonna come easy to you.

15:36.703 --> 15:38.638
*

15:38.671 --> 15:40.340
I think you're gonna have to

15:40.373 --> 15:43.643
work pretty hard
to become the person

15:43.676 --> 15:45.478
I know you can become.

15:46.646 --> 15:49.649
And it will make
the big victories in life

15:49.682 --> 15:51.118
that much more special

15:51.151 --> 15:53.486
when you have to work
a little harder for them.

16:03.963 --> 16:05.632
Do you know
what Dr. Jaffey told us

16:05.665 --> 16:08.368
-when we went
for your last checkup?
-Hmm?

16:08.401 --> 16:11.638
He told us he thinks that
you're gonna be really tall,

16:11.671 --> 16:14.941
like over six feet tall.

16:14.974 --> 16:18.178
-Really?
-Mm-hmm. "A real jock,"
is what he said.

16:18.211 --> 16:20.313
Oh, God. That'd be so great.

16:20.347 --> 16:22.615
Yeah.

16:22.649 --> 16:24.284
(Rebecca scoffs)

16:24.317 --> 16:26.153
(sighs) I feel better.

16:26.186 --> 16:29.022
Well, I'm glad.

16:29.056 --> 16:30.857
I think.

16:30.890 --> 16:33.826
(chuckles):
